Introduction

Soojin (formerly known as N.Na) is a South Korean singer and dancer under BRD Communications. She is a former member of the girl group (G)I-DLE and a pre-debut member of VIVIDIVA.

Using the stage name N.Na, Soojin was part of the pre-debut lineup for the girl group VIVIDIVA. However, she left the company before the group debuted in 2015. N.Na is named after Vienna, Austria, because Vienna is the city of music, romance, and youth and Soojin embodies that.

In 2016 she joined Cube Entertainment and in 2017-2018 she appeared in Soyeon's ((G)I-DLE) solo music videos for songs "Jelly" and "Idle Song" as an unknown dancer wearing a white fox mask. Soojin debuted as a member of (G)I-DLE on May 2, 2018, with their mini-album "I Am" and the title song "Latata".

On March 4, 2021, it was announced that Soojin would temporarily halt all activities following allegations of bullying by former classmates. On August 14, Cube Entertainment announced that Soojin had officially withdrawn from (G)I-DLE, though she will remain under the same agency.

On March 5, 2022, Cube Entertainment announced that they officially terminated Soojin's contract after police investigations concluded that the accusers were not guilty of spreading false information. On September 8, Soojin's legal representative released a statement on her behalf, "The school's Autonomous Committee for School Violence Countermeasures found her not guilty. Instead, they discovered she had been a victim of bullying, and no further legal action will be pursued."

On October 16, 2023, Soojin signed an exclusive contract with BRD Communications and debuted on November 8, 2023, with her first EP "Agassy".
